I've skimmed this on the assumption it's in good faith. This looks good to me, and means that when grepping for untriaged porting notes we can exclude these.

I've done a manual pass through this and it looks fine, but there are four instances which are not of the form "the following theorem used to be simp in lean 3 and we're removing the attribute here", which I've flagged as perhaps needing further attention.

Thanks :tada:

bors merge
What is going on with this one? Is this a bug in the simpNF linter?
This question should probably be reported in the corresponding issue #10618.
Now this question can be found [here](https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/issues/10618#issuecomment-1955018632).
And this one!
Now this question can be found [here](https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/issues/10618#issuecomment-1955023023).
Is this the correct solution for this problem?
Now this question can be found [here](https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/issues/10618#issuecomment-1955028349).
"and removed norm_cast attribute" seems to be an independent thing which we might also want to track? Maybe add a second porting note `-- porting note: removed norm_cast attribute`?

@pitmonticone I think this is a good idea.

(Please indicate whether you've processed the comments by Kevin.)
@jcommelin Yes, I'll integrate it as soon as I come back home this evening.
@jcommelin Added the new porting note as suggested by @kbuzzard (and solved merge conflicts).
